AGI -&nbsp;&nbsp;Without the works of mitigation "would have been an authentic disaster". This was said by the governor of Veneto Luca Zaia speaking in the margin of a press point organized at the headquarters of the Civil Protection of Marghera (Venice) to make the point on the wave of bad weather that hit the Veneto in the last hours.
&nbsp;
"But we have put into operation all the lamination basins - he then added - 6 basins in operation, 5 in Vicenza and one in Verona give demonstration of the intensity of the rain. In a few hours we had plenty of water: 229mm. If we hadn't had the basins today, we'd go around Vicenza with the gommoni." Finally, it has added, of a rainfall that has occurred in 24 hours.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The next 24 hours still require maximum attention and maximum alert. The perturbation should then move towards the east towards Treviso and Belluno". Thus the governor of Veneto Luca Zaia making a point on the wave of bad weather that in the last hours has fallen on the Veneto.
&nbsp;
"It was an exceptional phenomenon for seasonality and characteristics - it then added - intense showers in a very short time that do not even allow the discharge of surface water. It is as if we threw water in the sink even if this works perfectly it fails to flow so high water."

