The number of investigators rose from 31 to 33. At Massimo Temussi, former commissioner of the Ats (Health Protection Company, then replaced by the Ares) and now general director of the active policies of the work, investigated for abuse of office and revelation of secret of office, is added the health manager Giorgio Carboni. "I have never committed offenses and thought it was all about this," said Mariotti.&nbsp.
